I recommend using Storyboard to change the Style reference instead of using Setter directly.

```xml
&lt;VisualState x:Name=&quot;Pressed&quot;&gt;
    &lt;Storyboard&gt;
        &lt;ObjectAnimationUsingKeyFrames Storyboard.TargetName=&quot;HorizontalThumb&quot; Storyboard.TargetProperty=&quot;Style&quot;&gt;
            &lt;DiscreteObjectKeyFrame KeyTime=&quot;0&quot; Value=&quot;{StaticResource SliderPointerOverThumbStyle}&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/ObjectAnimationUsingKeyFrames&gt;
    &lt;/Storyboard&gt;
&lt;/VisualState&gt;
```

In addition, the level of using `TemplateBinding` in `AcrylicBrush` is too deep. At this time, AcrylicBrush can&#39;t get the value of `Foreground`. This is not a good practice. I suggest you assign value directly to AcrylicBrush instead of using TemplateBinding, like:

```xml
&lt;Ellipse
        x:Name=&quot;ellipse&quot;
        Fill=&quot;{StaticResource MediaSliderThumbFillBrush}&quot;
        StrokeThickness=&quot;3.2&quot;&gt;
     &lt;Ellipse.Stroke&gt;
          &lt;AcrylicBrush
                       BackgroundSource=&quot;Backdrop&quot;
                       FallbackColor=&quot;{ThemeResource xxx}&quot;
                       TintColor=&quot;{ThemeResource xxx}&quot;
                       TintOpacity=&quot;0.75&quot; /&gt;
     &lt;/Ellipse.Stroke&gt;
&lt;/Ellipse&gt;
```

In short, use `TemplateBinding` on control properties instead of brush resources.

Best regards.

