I came across the same error `Caused by: java.lang.NoSuchFieldError: ASCII` after upgrading to Android 3.5 which was caused by having an old version of the android gradle build tools.

In my case what fixed the issue was upgrading from tools 3.2.1 to 3.5.0.

You can do this in the top level `build.gradle` (not the app one that is). In the `buildscript.dependencies` closure change it to 3.5.0 or higher if available:

```
buildscript {    
    repositories {
        ...
    }

    dependencies {
        // upgrade the version of the tools here
        classpath &#39;com.android.tools.build:gradle:3.5.0&#39;
        ...
    }
}
```

You may need to also upgrade your gradle wrapper, since 3.5.0 is not compatible with old versions of gradle. 

Since you are using Android Studio follow this answer to upgrade the wrapper: [How to upgrade gradle][1].

  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/17727645/how-to-update-gradle-in-android-studio

